The evidence with the title 'Salary raises: understanding cost of living vs. merit pay increases ' says Apr 28, 2010  ... Cost of living adjustments mean exactly that : what you are paid goes up  ... Any employer that does not recognize this as an annual “ merit ” increase or  ... Employee has seen total cash comp . Go down about 2 percent in the last year,  ... When inflation is 9 percent , a 5 percent pay increase is a real wage cut . 
